name: Travel_Planning_System-Admin_Services
description: This project was created using Spring Boot and Microservice Architecture.

name: C4-microservices-fc
description: Repository created for study, where I created a software systems architecture model using c4-model, from the microservices-based architecture module of the Full-Cycle course.

name: ecom-microservice
description: This repository hosts a microservice application that transforms a tightly coupled ecommerce system into a loosely coupled one. It includes six services, with five built in Django and one in Flask, adhering to REST principles for synchronous actions. HTML templates are centralized in the Gateway service for easy management.

name: Retail-Product-Management-System
description: Microservices using Spring Boot and Spring Cloud. JWT authentication using Spring Security through ApiGateway. Implemented Fault Tolerance using Resilience4J (Retry and Fallback Methods). Configured Feign Client for API calls. Containerised using Docker and created docker-compose.yaml file. Implemented Distributed Tracing with Zipkin and RabbitMQ.

name: Build-the-Backend-System-for-a-Car-Website
description: In this project you will have the opportunity to create a REST-based Vehicles API that communicates with a location and pricing service using Spring Boot, along with converting the existing Pricing Service API to a microservice registered on a Eureka server.

name: NotificationTemplateFormatter
description: Related to  Manning's Microservices Notification System Design. A notification template formatter microservice with an API to create the merged template notification content that would be sent to the customer via SMS or email.

name: kitaplik-online
description: This  repository contains a microservices-based solution for efficient library book management. Utilizing modular microservices architecture, the system offers features such as book catalog management. Built with technologies like Spring Boot, Docker, this project ensures scalability, flexibility, and easy integration for libraries.

name: net7-observability
description: This repository enables observability in C# applications using OpenTelemetry. Improve performance and debugging with OpenTelemetry's APIs. Ideal for distributed systems and microservices architecture. Covers tracing, metrics, logging, and storage.
